execute(address,bytes).details: Emits an {Execute} event. Requirements: - The caller must be either the owner or an envoy with permission. - `target` must be a contract.

params.data: Function selector plus ABI encoded data.
params.target: The address of the target contract.

returns.response: The response received from the target contract, if any.

execute(address,bytes).notice: Delegate calls to the provided target contract by forwarding the data. It returns the data it gets back, and bubbles up any potential revert.

owner().notice: The address of the owner account or contract, which controls the proxy.

registry().notice: The address of the registry that has deployed this proxy.

documentation.text: @notice Thrown when a target contract reverts without a specified reason.
@notice Thrown when an unauthorized account tries to execute a delegate call.
@notice Thrown when the fallback function fails to find an installed plugin for the method selector.
@notice Thrown when a plugin execution reverts without a specified reason.
@notice Thrown when a non-contract address is passed as the target.
@notice Emitted when a target contract is delegate called.
@notice Emitted when a plugin is run for a provided method.
@notice The address of the owner account or contract, which controls the proxy.
@notice The address of the registry that has deployed this proxy.

@title IPRBProxy
 @notice Proxy contract to compose transactions on behalf of the owner.
